## Mode Status Recording

### Git Notes Extension

**CRITICAL**: The selected mode must be recorded in Git notes for subsequent flow identification:

```json
{
  "ticket": "FE-1234",
  "operationMode": "cautious|multi-task|fast|default",
  "modeConfig": {
    // mode-specific config
  },
  // ... other fields
}
```

### Mode-specific Config

#### Cautious mode
```json
{
  "operationMode": "cautious",
  "modeConfig": {
    "confirmEachStep": true,
    "minimumChanges": true,
    "rollbackPlan": true
  }
}
```

#### Multi-task mode
```json
{
  "operationMode": "multi-task",
  "modeConfig": {
    "parentTicket": "FE-1234",
    "subTasks": ["FE-1234-1", "FE-1234-2"],
    "currentPhase": 1,
    "totalPhases": 2,
    "commitPerPhase": true,
    "singleMR": true
  }
}
```

#### Fast mode
```json
{
  "operationMode": "fast",
  "modeConfig": {
    "tickets": ["FE-1234", "FE-1235", "FE-1236"],
    "currentIndex": 0,
    "totalTasks": 3,
    "autoProgress": true,
    "branchNameStrategy": "feature-ticket",
    "notifyAfterAll": true
  }
}
```

#### Default mode
```json
{
  "operationMode": "default",
  "modeConfig": {}
}
```

